# Resume PDF generation

`static/resume.pdf` is generated by `resume/generate-pdf.js` using Chromium
**print-to-PDF** via Puppeteer (`page.pdf({ preferCSSPageSize: true })`). It depends on the
`@media print` rules and `@page { size: 210mm 297mm }` in `src/pages/resume.module.css`.
Print mode auto-hides the Docusaurus navbar/footer, so they never appear in the PDF.

## Do NOT

- Do **not** switch to screen capture (`page.emulateMediaType('screen')` or element
  screenshots). Screen mode re-shows the sticky navbar (the hamburger menu) and bakes it
  into the PDF.
- Do **not** pass `clip` to `page.pdf()` — it is **not** a valid option (only
  `page.screenshot()` supports `clip`). It is silently ignored and produces
  duplicated/cut pages.
- Do **not** make PDF pages non-A4 or rewrite the generator to "fix" content overflow.

## To fit content on a page (the right fix)

If a page is slightly too tall for A4, trim font-size / line-height / margins in the
`@media print` block of `resume.module.css` — the MS-Word "fit to page" nudge. Verify each
page stays within 297mm and the output is exactly 2 A4 pages.

## Regenerate locally

After `npm start`:
`RESUME_URL=http://localhost:3000/resume npm run generate-resume`
